                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <ref target="#ms_i1.4 #ms_i1.5"/>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works
                    There is no columetric layout
                  </desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#1r" facs="001"/><desc>Two women holding their heads as two evil soldiers with spears approach</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#6r" facs="006"/><desc>Woman standing before a dead or sleeping saint reclining in lower front. One bird is behind the man, another ascends toward the upper right</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d3">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#26v #37r #51r #80v #107v #110v #117r" facs="027 037 051 081 108 111 117"/> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#44v" facs="045"/> (a line of full stops connected with red and black lines);
                      <locus target="#66v" facs="067"/> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    The first quire, containing a fragment of the Song of Songs, has been dislocated
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#1v" facs="002"/>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#72" facs="072"/>
                      red yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#97 #101 #107" facs="097 101 107"/>
                      white yarn is sewn into the fore edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    marginal notation throughout
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#8r #8v #28v #40r" facs="008 029 040"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#113v" facs="114"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#34v #108r" facs="035 108"/>).
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                      This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, a line is too long and has to be completed above or below the end of the line. (e.g., <locus target="#4v #33v" facs="005 034"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 162 x 158 x 78 mm, four altered Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards, front cover and first two quires have been reattached with newer string.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
